{"id":153678,"date":"2023-03-29T10:55:52","date_gmt":"2023-03-29T05:25:52","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=153678"},"modified":"2023-04-03T15:55:40","modified_gmt":"2023-04-03T10:25:40","slug":"sunny-varkey","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/","title":{"rendered":"Sunny Varkey Wiki, Age, Wife, Family, Biography &#038; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-153993\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey.jpg\" alt=\"Sunny Varkey\" width=\"515\" height=\"420\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey.jpg 735w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-300x245.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 515px) 100vw, 515px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Sunny Varkey is an Indian-born Dubai-based entrepreneur, philanthropist, and educationist who is the founder of Global Education Management Systems (GEMS), the world&#8217;s largest operator of private kindergarten-to-grade-12 schools.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce2cb96a6c\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/label><input type=\"checkbox\"  id=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce2cb96a6c\"  aria-label=\"Toggle\" \/><nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#WikiBiography\" title=\"Wiki\/Biography\">Wiki\/Biography<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#Physical_Appearance\" title=\"Physical Appearance\">Physical Appearance<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#Family\" title=\"Family\">Family<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#Parents_Siblings\" title=\"Parents &amp; Siblings\">Parents &amp; Siblings<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#Wife_Children\" title=\"Wife &amp; Children\">Wife &amp; Children<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#Religion\" title=\"Religion\">Religion<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#SignatureAutograph\" title=\"Signature\/Autograph\">Signature\/Autograph<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#Career\" title=\"Career\">Career<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#Banker\" title=\"Banker\">Banker<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#Entrepreneur\" title=\"Entrepreneur\">Entrepreneur<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#Philanthropist\" title=\"Philanthropist\">Philanthropist<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#Awards_Honours\" title=\"Awards &amp; Honours\">Awards &amp; Honours<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-13\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#Net_Worth\" title=\"Net Worth\">Net Worth<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-14\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sunny-varkey\/#FactsTrivia\" title=\"Facts\/Trivia\">Facts\/Trivia<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"WikiBiography\"><\/span>Wiki\/Biography<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Sunny Varkey was born in 1957 (<strong>age 67 years; as of 2023<\/strong>) in Ranni, Kerala, India. Sunny&#8217;s parents shifted to Dubai when he was two years old. In 1981, Sunny was sent to India, where he enrolled at the Infant Jesus Anglo-Indian Boys&#8217; School in Kollam, Kerala. Thereafter, he enrolled at J. M. J. Catholic Boarding School in Mumbai. He later went back to Dubai, where he enrolled at St. Mary&#8217;s Catholic High School and cleared his O levels examination following which he enrolled at the Bembridge School in the United Kingdom, where he pursued his A levels for a year. In an interview, Sunny said that since Dubai back then had no schools for A-level education, many students from UAE went to the UK. Talking about it, he said,<\/p>\n<blockquote><p>After I passed my O levels, my parents decided to send me to the UK to complete my A levels at Bembridge College in the Isle of Wight. Many students from the UAE used to go there to complete their studies, as there was no higher education available in Dubai at the time.&#8221;<\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p>Later, he came back to Dubai and completed the A-levels at the British Council.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Physical_Appearance\"><\/span>Physical Appearance<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><strong>Height (approx.):<\/strong> 5&#8242; 10&#8243;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Hair Colour:\u00a0<\/strong>Salt and Pepper<\/p>\n<p><strong>Eye Colour:<\/strong> Dark Brown<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_153995\" style=\"width: 370px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-photo-of-Sunny-Varkey-with-UNESCO-Director-General-Audrey-Azoulay.jpeg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-153995\" class=\"wp-image-153995\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-photo-of-Sunny-Varkey-with-UNESCO-Director-General-Audrey-Azoulay.jpeg\" alt=\"A photo of Sunny Varkey with UNESCO's Director-General Audrey Azoulay\" width=\"360\" height=\"507\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-photo-of-Sunny-Varkey-with-UNESCO-Director-General-Audrey-Azoulay.jpeg 398w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-photo-of-Sunny-Varkey-with-UNESCO-Director-General-Audrey-Azoulay-213x300.jpeg 213w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-153995\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A photo of Sunny Varkey with UNESCO&#8217;s Director-General Audrey Azoulay<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Family\"><\/span>Family<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Sunny Varkey was born into a Syrian Christian family in Kerala. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_153678_1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_153678_1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.theguardian.com\/education\/2005\/dec\/13\/schools.newschools\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Guardian<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Parents_Siblings\"><\/span><strong>Parents &amp; Siblings<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>His father K. S. Varkey (deceased) was a banker and educationist. His mother Mariamma Varkey (deceased) was an educationist. His sister, Susan Mathews, is an educationist.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_153997\" style=\"width: 413px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-picture-of-Sunny-Varkeys-parents.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-153997\" class=\" wp-image-153997\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-picture-of-Sunny-Varkeys-parents.jpg\" alt=\"A picture of Sunny Varkey's parents\" width=\"403\" height=\"273\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-picture-of-Sunny-Varkeys-parents.jpg 468w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-picture-of-Sunny-Varkeys-parents-300x203.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 403px) 100vw, 403px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-153997\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A picture of Sunny Varkey&#8217;s parents<\/p><\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Wife_Children\"><\/span><strong>Wife &amp; Children<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Sunny Varkey is married to Shirley Varkey, who works in GEMS Education.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_153999\" style=\"width: 371px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-with-his-wife.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-153999\" class=\" wp-image-153999\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-with-his-wife.jpg\" alt=\"Sunny Varkey with his wife Shirley Varkey\" width=\"361\" height=\"639\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-with-his-wife.jpg 452w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-with-his-wife-170x300.jpg 170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 361px) 100vw, 361px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-153999\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Sunny Varkey with his wife Shirley Varkey<\/p><\/div>\n<p>His son, Jay Varkey, is the Group Executive Director at GEMS Education. His other son, Dino Varkey, is the CEO of GEMS Education.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_154000\" style=\"width: 410px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Jay-Varkey-with-his-father-Sunny-Varkey.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-154000\" class=\" wp-image-154000\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Jay-Varkey-with-his-father-Sunny-Varkey.jpg\" alt=\"Jay Varkey with his father Sunny Varkey\" width=\"400\" height=\"658\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Jay-Varkey-with-his-father-Sunny-Varkey.jpg 486w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Jay-Varkey-with-his-father-Sunny-Varkey-182x300.jpg 182w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-154000\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Jay Varkey with his father Sunny Varkey<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_154004\" style=\"width: 413px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-photo-of-Sunny-Varkey-with-his-son-Dino-Varkey.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-154004\" class=\" wp-image-154004\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-photo-of-Sunny-Varkey-with-his-son-Dino-Varkey.jpg\" alt=\"A photo of Sunny Varkey with his son Dino Varkey\" width=\"403\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-photo-of-Sunny-Varkey-with-his-son-Dino-Varkey.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-photo-of-Sunny-Varkey-with-his-son-Dino-Varkey-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-photo-of-Sunny-Varkey-with-his-son-Dino-Varkey-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 403px) 100vw, 403px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-154004\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A photo of Sunny Varkey with his son Dino Varkey<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Religion\"><\/span>Religion<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Sunny Varkey follows Christianity.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"SignatureAutograph\"><\/span>Signature\/Autograph<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<div id=\"attachment_154005\" style=\"width: 250px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Signature-of-Sunny-Varkey.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-154005\" class=\" wp-image-154005\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Signature-of-Sunny-Varkey.jpg\" alt=\"Signature of Sunny Varkey\" width=\"240\" height=\"177\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Signature-of-Sunny-Varkey.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Signature-of-Sunny-Varkey-300x221.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Signature-of-Sunny-Varkey-768x565.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 240px) 100vw, 240px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-154005\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Signature of Sunny Varkey<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career\"><\/span>Career<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Banker\"><\/span><strong>Banker<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>After completing his formal education, Sunny joined the Standard Chartered Bank&#8217;s Al Shamal branch in Dubai. In an interview, Sunny said that he decided to become a banker rather than help his parents run Our Own English High School, established in Dubai in 1968, as he believed that his way of running the school would lead to clashes with his parents. After working for a few years in the bank, he tendered his resignation as the pay scale of the bank was low and was not enough for Sunny to save money and establish his business. While giving an interview, Sunny said,<\/p>\n<blockquote><p>I was preparing some accounts and saw, quite by accident, that my manager, who had worked with the bank for 22 years, earned a salary of Dh6,000 a month. I was shocked, and calculated that even with subsequent payrises for maybe ten years, I would never be able to earn even Dh10,000 a month. I decided right away to quit and start my own business.&#8221;<\/p><\/blockquote>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Entrepreneur\"><\/span><strong>Entrepreneur<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>After quitting his job as a banker, Sunny Varkey started a maintenance company named Chicago Maintenance Company in 1978. Sunny said that he decided to give a Western name to the company to attract business from Western companies. In 1979, he founded a trading company named J.M.J. Trading. In 1980, he along with a partner opened a hotel named The Dubai Plaza, which was later renamed Rydges Plaza Dubai. In the same year, Varkey took over the control of Our Own English High School from his parents after the Dubai Municipality wrote a letter to his parents, asking them to construct a proper infrastructure to continue teaching. Thereafter, Sunny appointed Qassim Sultan, the then-director of Dubai Municipality, as the school&#8217;s patron and bought a piece of land to construct some portacabins in which the classes resumed.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_154006\" style=\"width: 370px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-photo-of-Our-Own-English-School-taken-in-the-1980s.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-154006\" class=\"wp-image-154006 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-photo-of-Our-Own-English-School-taken-in-the-1980s.jpg\" alt=\"A photo of Our Own English High School taken in the 1980s\" width=\"360\" height=\"233\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-photo-of-Our-Own-English-School-taken-in-the-1980s.jpg 360w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-photo-of-Our-Own-English-School-taken-in-the-1980s-300x194.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-154006\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A photo of Our Own English High School taken in the 1980s<\/p><\/div>\n<p>In 2000, Sunny established the GEMS Education Group and founded several schools under its flagship in the UAE. In 2003, Sunny acquired the Sherfield School in Hampshire, United Kingdom. Thereafter, he purchased ten more schools in Northern England. In 2004, the GEMS Education Group established several schools in India as well as in Pakistan. GEMS Education became a part of the World Economic Forum&#8217;s Global Growth Companies in June 2010. GEMS became the Clinton Global Initiative&#8217;s strategic partner in the same year. In 2011, he established a school in Nairobi, Kenya. In 2012, he founded two schools in Chicago. The schools functioning under GEMS Education provide education in International Baccalaureate (IB), Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE), and Indian Certificate of Secondary Education (ICSE).<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Philanthropist\"><\/span>Philanthropist<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Sunny Varkey founded the Varkey GEMS Foundation (now known as Varkey Foundation) in 2010 with the intent of providing free-of-cost education to the poor and the needy. The foundation provides education to a hundred poor children for one child, who enrols in a school operated by GEMS. In collaboration with UNESCO and the Ministry of Education of UAE, Varkey Foundation initiated an annual Global Education and Skills Forum in 2013. Thereafter, the foundation started a program named MGCubed &#8211; Making Ghana Girls Great to provide quality education to underprivileged girl children. The Varkey Foundation has worked in close conjecture with many international NGOs including UNICEF, the Clinton Global Initiative, Oxfam, Pratham, Dubai Cares, and the Brookings Institution.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Awards_Honours\"><\/span>Awards &amp; Honours<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Global Indian Business Award (2007)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>CEO Middle East Award in the Corporate Social Responsibility category (2007)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Outstanding Asian Businessman of the Year (2007)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Rajiv Gandhi Award for Eminent Educationist (2008)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>India&#8217;s fourth-highest civilian award, Padma Shri (2009) <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_153678_1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_153678_1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/thehinduimages.com\/details-page.php?id=107947705\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Sunny Varkey&#8217;s photo on The Hindu<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Public Recognition Award from the Government of Russia (2011)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Award of Distinction by the UAE government (2011)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Middle East Excellence CEO of the Year in the Knowledge Development and Education Partnership category (2012)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Education Business Leader of the Year Award by Gulf Business Industry (2012)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Honorary Doctorate by Heriot-Watt University (2012)\n<p><div id=\"attachment_154008\" style=\"width: 412px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-picture-of-Sunny-Varkey-receiving-the-Honourary-degree.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-154008\" class=\"wp-image-154008\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-picture-of-Sunny-Varkey-receiving-the-Honourary-degree.jpg\" alt=\"A picture of Sunny Varkey receiving the Honorary degree\" width=\"402\" height=\"279\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-picture-of-Sunny-Varkey-receiving-the-Honourary-degree.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-picture-of-Sunny-Varkey-receiving-the-Honourary-degree-300x208.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-picture-of-Sunny-Varkey-receiving-the-Honourary-degree-768x533.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-154008\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A picture of Sunny Varkey receiving the Honorary degree<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Arabian Business Achievement Award (2017)\n<p><div id=\"attachment_154013\" style=\"width: 419px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-holding-the-Arabian-Business-Achievement-Award.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-154013\" class=\" wp-image-154013\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-holding-the-Arabian-Business-Achievement-Award.jpg\" alt=\"Sunny Varkey holding the Arabian Business Achievement Award\" width=\"409\" height=\"448\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-holding-the-Arabian-Business-Achievement-Award.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-holding-the-Arabian-Business-Achievement-Award-274x300.jpg 274w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 409px) 100vw, 409px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-154013\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Sunny Varkey holding the Arabian Business Achievement Award<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Entrepreneur of the Year by The Asian Awards (2018)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Net_Worth\"><\/span>Net Worth<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>On 28 March 2023, his net worth was estimated to be $3 billion.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_154009\" style=\"width: 481px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-screenshot-of-Sunny-Varkeys-net-worth.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-154009\" class=\" wp-image-154009\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-screenshot-of-Sunny-Varkeys-net-worth.jpg\" alt=\"A screenshot of Sunny Varkey's net worth\" width=\"471\" height=\"304\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-screenshot-of-Sunny-Varkeys-net-worth.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-screenshot-of-Sunny-Varkeys-net-worth-300x194.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-screenshot-of-Sunny-Varkeys-net-worth-768x495.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 471px) 100vw, 471px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-154009\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A screenshot of Sunny Varkey&#8217;s net worth<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"FactsTrivia\"><\/span>Facts\/Trivia<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2012, he was appointed as the UNESCO Goodwill Ambassador.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_154012\" style=\"width: 411px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-holding-the-certificate-that-he-received-after-becoming-the-UNESCO-Goodwill-Ambassador.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-154012\" class=\" wp-image-154012\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-holding-the-certificate-that-he-received-after-becoming-the-UNESCO-Goodwill-Ambassador.jpg\" alt=\"Sunny Varkey holding the certificate that he received after becoming the UNESCO Goodwill Ambassador\" width=\"401\" height=\"251\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-holding-the-certificate-that-he-received-after-becoming-the-UNESCO-Goodwill-Ambassador.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-holding-the-certificate-that-he-received-after-becoming-the-UNESCO-Goodwill-Ambassador-300x188.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/Sunny-Varkey-holding-the-certificate-that-he-received-after-becoming-the-UNESCO-Goodwill-Ambassador-768x480.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 401px) 100vw, 401px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-154012\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Sunny Varkey holding the certificate that he received after becoming the UNESCO Goodwill Ambassador<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In the same year, Sunny Varkey was featured on the cover of Global Citizen Magazine.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_154010\" style=\"width: 419px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/The-cover-page-of-the-Global-Citizen-Magazine.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-154010\" class=\" wp-image-154010\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/The-cover-page-of-the-Global-Citizen-Magazine.jpg\" alt=\"The cover page of the Global Citizen Magazine\" width=\"409\" height=\"494\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/The-cover-page-of-the-Global-Citizen-Magazine.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/The-cover-page-of-the-Global-Citizen-Magazine-249x300.jpg 249w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 409px) 100vw, 409px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-154010\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The cover page of the Global Citizen Magazine<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2018, Sunny donated $1.4 million to Kerala Aid Fund.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Sunny Varkey&#8217;s favourite quote is &#8220;I don&#8217;t believe in giving up even when I hit a hard wall.&#8221;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Sunny Varkey used to sell fruits when he was studying in Kerala. While giving an interview, he said,<br \/>\n<blockquote><p>I started to sell fruits on the streets in Kerala, just to make more money. I had always dreamt of becoming a businessman, since childhood it was my dream.&#8221;<\/p><\/blockquote>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div class=\"489bcfb86580b123547338c91db0eff2\" data-index=\"3\" style=\"float: none; margin:3px 0 3px 0; text-align:center;\">\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\r\n     style=\"display:block\"\r\n     data-ad-format=\"autorelaxed\"\r\n     data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-6769524711517462\"\r\n     data-ad-slot=\"2473600074\"><\/ins>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"font-size: 0px; height: 0px; line-height: 0px; margin: 0; padding: 0; clear: both;\"><\/div><div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_label_expand_153678_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">References<\/span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_button_plus_153678_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">[+]<\/span><span><\/span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_button_minus_153678_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button collapsed\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_153678_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">[\u2212]<\/span><\/p><\/div> <div id=\"footnote_references_container_153678_1\" class=\"collapsed\"><table class=\"footnotes_table footnote-reference-container\"><caption class=\"accessibility\">References<\/caption> <tbody> \r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi pointer\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_153678_1_1\" class=\"footnote_backlink\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>1<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.theguardian.com\/education\/2005\/dec\/13\/schools.newschools\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Guardian<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi pointer\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_153678_1_2\" class=\"footnote_backlink\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>2<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/thehinduimages.com\/details-page.php?id=107947705\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Sunny Varkey&#8217;s photo on The Hindu<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n <\/tbody> <\/table> <\/div><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Sunny Varkey is an Indian-born Dubai-based entrepreneur, philanthropist, and educationist who is the founder of Global Education Management Systems (GEMS), the world&#8217;s largest operator of private kindergarten-to-grade-12 schools. Wiki\/Biography Sunny Varkey was born in 1957 (age 67 years; as of 2023) in Ranni, Kerala, India. Sunny&#8217;s parents shifted to Dubai when he was two years old. In 1981, Sunny was sent to India, where he enrolled at the Infant Jesus Anglo-Indian Boys&#8217; School in Kollam, Kerala. Thereafter, he enrolled at J. M. J. Catholic Boarding School in Mumbai. He later went back to Dubai, where he enrolled at St. Mary&#8217;s <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":50,"featured_media":153993,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[19],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/153678"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/50"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=153678"}],"version-history":[{"count":15,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/153678\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":154686,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/153678\/revisions\/154686"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/153993"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=153678"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=153678"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=153678"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}